2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper deals with modeling and solving optimization problems, which is a common task in machine learning. 
3. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper proposes a new language (SC-ProbLog) for modeling SCOPs, which falls under the domain of programming languages. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the use of Ordered Binary Decision Diagrams (OBDDs) and a new propagator for solving SCOPs, which are data structures and algorithms commonly used in computer science. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes a new method for solving SCOPs, which can be seen as a software engineering problem.
